The '''Shalkani''' ({{lang-ur|شلکنی}}) is a village in northern [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]], northwestern [[Pakistan]]. Shalkani is located approximately at 6&nbsp;km distance from [[Peshawar]] to [[Dir, Pakistan|Dir]] GT Road.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://putaj.org/index.php/science/article/view/230/26 | title=Handling The Scarce Mountains’ Resources: Role Of Indigenous Tenure Arrangements In Land Management In Roghani Valley Northern Pakistan |author=Fazlul Haq |display-authors=etal |publisher=University of Peshawar }}</ref>

==Location==
Shalkani is located on the left side of Panjkoora River, about 26 kilometers from [[Timergara]]. To the north side of Shalkani Jelar Dara is located, to the south is [[Shalpalam]], to the east is Akhagram and to the west is Luqman Banda, and Shalkani is located as a small valley in center of them.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://wikimapia.org/15373632/Shalkani-Fazli-Haq-M-Phil | title=Fazli Haq M.Phil Map on Wikimapia }}</ref>

